                            "optionText": "$!$U = -\\frac{1}{2}\\frac{GMm}{r}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "f4c0576428be428a83eef",
                    "stepText": "Now compute the gravitational potential energy at perigee. Use $!$r_1 = 7000\\,\\text{km}$!$ converted to meters, along with values for $!$G$!$, $!$M$!$, and $!$m$!$. Perform the multiplication and division carefully.",
